Inordinate Deſire is a Fire blown off from the Hearth, or an Elementum extra Locum, the Fidiculae Fidicularum where Men ſuffer exquiſite Torments. It's every Evil or their Cauſe; for what is Ambition but nimia Honoris Cupiditas, what Iracundiae but fervens Vindicta Appetitus, what Covetouſneſs but Auri Fames; whence Homicides, Rapine, Luxury, Treacheries, Tyrannies, Factions but from this?—Seneca hath ſomething to it;


Deſire of Gain betray'd the Truſt,

And Bedlam rage with every Luſt

Attends the Mind, then Thirſt of Sway;

The Leſs is made the Greater's Prey

While Power is Law.
